tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly decreased HbA1c, creatinine, and total CO₂, with all other parameters within normal limits. The low HbA1c may reflect recent changes in glucose metabolism or possible anemia, while low creatinine is often not clinically significant in elderly males with reduced muscle mass. Slightly low CO₂ may suggest mild metabolic acidosis or compensation. No acute abnormalities detected; clinical correlation recommended.
